Indeed, it is very close. It is the second time I fail to find a similar puzzle... I want to say that having a more advanced research bar would be better :p (looking for words in statement or at least tags). In order to support my puzzle, I will say the main differences are:
- more parameters, in particular the fact that there are cells more valuable than others ;
- mecanism of prevention instead of being limited to operate on fire ;
- the fact that is is an optimization game make it more interesting I think. (And as suggested Konstant, we can even remove the success goals in order to focus on saving each cell).

About the optimization goal, I believe there is no polynomial solution which will give an optimal result for all test cases one can imagine (I didn't prove that ^^ ). Then the question will be whether the tests I imagined are enough for that or not.
